-- Essar Unit Bidding for $220 Billion in Gulf Projects, CEO Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-04-23T13:56:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/essar-unit-bidding-for-220-billion-in-gulf-projects-ceo-says.html
Essar Projects Ltd. is bidding for
engineering and construction contracts worth $220 billion in
 Saudi Arabia , Oman, Qatar, Kuwait and the  United Arab Emirates ,
President and Chief Executive Officer Alwyn Bowden said.  “We can’t win them all, but we will try to win a
considerable amount of these projects,” he said today in an
interview in Khobar, Saudi Arabia.  Most of the projects Essar is targeting in the Persian Gulf
region are in the oil and natural gas industries, Bowden said.
Essar Projects, a unit of India’s Essar Group, generates annual
revenue of about $2 billion, he said. The engineering and
construction company is based in Dubai in the U.A.E.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar, Saudi Arabia at 
